lection (Vesna v Fialtre, Chekhov Publishing House, New York, 1956). “Lik” reflects the miragy Riviera surroundings among which I composed it and attempts to create the impression of a stage performance engulfing a neurotic performer, though not quite in the way that the trapped actor expected when dreaming of such an experience.

The present English translation appeared first in The New Yorker, October 10, 1964, and was included in Nabokov’s Quartet, Phaedra Publishers, New York, 1966.

